First of all, I lived in London for three weeks in Recently, I am a teacher in a high school and the authorities in my country lets me stay it, improving my English. I would like to say that learning any languages is complicated to someone, whatever you come from, but in my opinion, there are many matter to discuss. A good way of this would be children. One child whose parents come from different countries is able to learn two languages at the same time, this child doesn't need to go abroad to learn a foreign language, but they are listening to their parents speaking English their native language all the time and this, let them learn without any difficulty. On the other hand, if you go abroad, you will be able to improve your English in an <unk>, in this case, your knowledge will be you with your stay there. To sum up, if you want to learn English, you don't need to go abroad, you can improve your English working hard at your own country. For example, doing exercises like listening and writing or you can meet with native people who speak English to do with them. But if you have one opportunity to go abroad, this would be so good for you and your English.

Moreover, if it is a really nice group, it is fun fun to work with them than to work alone. In conclusion, I believe that it's better to work as a team than to work on your own because they give you love, company and you could pass a very good time.

Many people believe that public transport will be replaced by private one in the nearest future. The main reason is the convenience of travelling by car in comparison with using public transport. Apart from that, there are many other benefits in buying a car instead of using buses or underground every day. First of all, an automobile gives such a valuable thing as privacy. For example, driving a car we can wear whatever we want and listen to music on any properties. If the car is large enough, it can be even a perfect place for sleep. Additionally, if we are eager to travel outside the town in order to have some rest from a daily rhythm of life, it will be more comfortable for us to use our cars. Only our own vehicle can provide us with an opportunity to find any quiet and pleasant place outside the city. Public transport can take us to not have to certain restrictions. Thus, it is clear that private transport such as auto numbers has plenty of advantages. On the other hand, we can be stuck with different problems while travelling by car. For instance, being in traffic jams, always stealings much our precious time. Car drivers are the typical reason for this phenomenon. It means that travelling by car can even be more dangerous than using public transport. Generally, buses are much more organized than automobile ones, therefore, accidents caused by public transport has causedy rarely. This makes travelling by public transport more safer. Thus, I would argue that driving a car requires much attention and understanding that careless behaviour on the road can make a serious damage to other people. In conclusion, I believe that public transport will eventually lose its Fance due to the fact that all people want to be independent and travel on their own.
